{
  "stem": "27507.11",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she was well-established in Tel Aviv, so I stayed for a few weeks with her.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then I went back to my parents, and my parents were in some kind of a camp for [INAUDIBLE], which was--",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "New immigrants, which was quite all right, but I was not enthusiastic about it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So because I was already, after the war, in Zionist movement in [HEBREW] I went to a kibbutz [HEBREW] to a group of youth who [HEBREW] and [HEBREW], not far--",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--from [INAUDIBLE], and stayed there for another-- for two years, working and studying and so on, learning Hebrew, which I didn't know any to start.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then I left that place in 1952 and went back to school and studied for another year and did my exams and went to the army, basically.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Served in the Israeli for--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was from '53 to '55.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And studies in Israel-- served in Israeli army.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then I made an entrance exams to Technion, to the institute of technology in Haifa, and got accepted for architecture and studied architecture for the next five years.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, then it is more complicated because my parents went to Brazil, so I--",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They didn't stay in Israel for good, no.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They went to Israel, which-- they went to Brazil because part of that family of ours who survived in Warsaw, they went to Brazil after the war.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother's sister, her sister that she was very fond of, lived in Rio de Janeiro, and she wanted to be near her.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So she went to Brazil once before and spent a long time, almost a year, and came back.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she more or less persuaded my father that they should go to Brazil.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Although my father did all his exams.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
